==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stovepipe
<hw>Stove"pipe`</hw> <pr>(st⟦omac⟧v"p⟦imac⟧p`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Pipe made of sheet iron in length and angular or curved pieces
fitting together, -- used to connect a portable stove with a chimney
flue.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stovepipe hat</b></col>, <cd>A tall silk hat with a brim,
worn commonly as an item of formal dress by gentlemen in the late
1800's.</cd> <mark>[Slang, U.S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stover</ent>⟦br⟧
